x4freetext: Delayed neutron emission spectra from thermal-neutron
fission of U-233,U-235,Pu-239,and Pu-241, from fast
neutron fission of Th-232,U-235,U-238,and Pu-239 and
from  high-energy neutron (14.7 MeV) fission of U-235
and U-238, for 6 groups of delayed neutron are
The evaluation is based on recent measurements of
delayed neutron spectra from 20 fission product
The data are presented in graphic forms and tables
with a convenient 54-energy-group structure are given
to facilitate their use in reactor calculations. But
only the first 30 groups are presented in tables,
since there are no measured spectra below 50 keV.
Average delayed neutron spectra are also provided for
A least-squares fit process was used in the evaluation.
OS. REACTION and Data units corrected
On. Half-lives added as coded information
